        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-10 07:37:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 11: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(15 inline comments)\n\nI suspect that while this patch is reducing the amount of allocation/freeing, it does look like it will be increasing stack usage noticeably because of \"env\" being passed/copied for 8 more bytes in lots of functions.\n\nCan you please run \"make checkstack\" before and after this patch is applied and built.  In particular:\n\n diff -U1 /tmp/checkstack{.orig,} | sort -k2\n\nwill produce a nice output, so we can compare each function side-by-side.\n\nThere are also many, many indentation problems.  Please run \"git show HEAD | checkpatch.pl -\" for this patch, then fix all of the errors and warnings that appear.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 11
    },
